---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | sudo make vibe"
  description="Learn about the blog and its mission"
>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--accent);">
        /about
      </h1>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div
        class="border-l-4 p-4 mb-8 font-mono"
        style="border-left-color: var(--accent); background-color: var(--bg-card);"
      >
        <span class="text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">$ whoami</span>
      </div>

      <p style="color: var(--text-primary);">
        I'm a developer and tinkerer exploring the intersection of
        <span style="color: #d33682;">vibe coding</span>,
        <span style="color: #859900;">AI</span>,
        <span style="color: #2aa198;">Linux</span>, and
        <span style="color: #dc322f;">Raspberry Pi</span>.
      </p>

      <h2
        class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4"
        style="color: var(--accent);"
      >
        What is vibe coding?
      </h2>
      <p style="color: var(--text-primary);">
        Vibe coding is using AI tools as a creative partner—maintaining flow
        while leveraging AI to accelerate from idea to implementation. It's not
        about letting AI do everything, but about reducing friction between
        thought and code.
      </p>

      <h2
        class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4"
        style="color: var(--accent);"
      >
        Why this blog?
      </h2>
      <p style="color: var(--text-primary);">
        I noticed a gap between the creative freedom of "vibe coding" and the
        discipline of systems engineering. This blog is my attempt to bridge
        that gap—to show that you can have both creative flow and technical
        depth.
      </p>

      <h2
        class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4"
        style="color: var(--accent);"
      >
        What to expect
      </h2>
      <ul
        class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2"
        style="color: var(--text-primary);"
      >
        <li>
          <strong>Vibe Coding:</strong> AI-assisted development tools and philosophy
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Linux:</strong> Terminal workflows, configs, and open-source tools
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Raspberry Pi:</strong> Homelab setups, GPIO projects, edge AI
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cybersecurity:</strong> Secure remote access, best practices
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Terminal Box - Kept only on About page -->
      <div
        class="p-6 rounded-lg border mt-8 font-mono"
        style="background-color: var(--bg-card); border-color: var(--border);"
      >
        <div>
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">$</span>
          <span style="color: var(--accent);">
            sudo make vibe --creative-environment</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="mt-2" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          > Building...<br />
          > Ready. Let's build something interesting.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
